Interview Summary

Docker Architecture:

Docker Client → sends commands.
Docker Daemon (dockerd) → manages Docker objects.
Docker Registry → stores images.
Images → templates.
Containers → running instances of images.
containerd → manages container lifecycle.
runc → creates and starts containers.
Linux Kernel → provides isolation (namespaces) and resource control (cgroups).

Execution Flow (docker run nginx):

User runs docker run nginx.
Docker Client sends the request to dockerd.
dockerd checks for the image locally.
If missing, it pulls the image from Docker Hub.
Creates a writable container layer.
Configures networking and mounts any volumes.
Applies CPU/memory limits (if specified).
containerd prepares the container.
runc creates the container using Linux namespaces and cgroups.
The image's CMD/ENTRYPOINT starts the application (Nginx), and the container begins running.
